<p>A problem by British puzzlist Hubert Phillips:</p>
<p>In writing home about an examination, five schoolgirls each made one true statement and one untrue one. The relevant passages:</p>
<p>Betty: Kitty was second in the examination. I was only third.<br />
Ethel: You&#8217;ll be glad to hear that I was top. Joan was second.<br />
Joan: I was third, and poor old Ethel was bottom.<br />
Kitty: I came out second. Mary was only fourth.<br />
Mary: I was fourth. Top place was taken by Betty.</p>
<p>In what order did they place?</p>

